22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EPlaying%20out%20on%20a%20vast%20and%20varied%20canvas%2C%20%3Ci%3ESam%20Bahadur%3C%2Fi%3E%20crams%20a%20lifetime%20into%20its%20two%20and%20a%20half%20hours.%20The%20film%20covers%20four%20decades%20of%20active%20military%20service%2C%20five%20wars%2C%20anti-insurgency%20operations%20and%20brushes%20with%20Prime%20Ministers.%20Inevitably%2C%20Meghna%20Gulzar's%20ambitious%20biographical%20film%20feels%20a%20tad%20rushed.%20But%20for%20sure%20it%20has%20nary%20a%20dull%20moment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20film%20fires%20on%20the%20fronts%20that%20matter.%20Driven%20by%20a%20high-spirited%20performance%20from%20Vicky%20Kaushal%2C%20it%20delivers%20a%20rounded%2C%20rousing%20portrait%20of%20Field%20Marshal%20Sam%20Hormusji%20Framji%20Jamshedji%20Manekshaw%2C%20a%20gentleman%20and%20an%20officer%20whose%20grit%20and%20gallantry%2C%20joie%20de%20vivre%2C%20power%20of%20repartee%20and%20an%20unwavering%20sense%20of%20purpose%20are%20the%20stuff%20of%20legend.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20intense%20character%20study%20more%20than%20an%20action-heavy%20war%20movie%2C%20%3Ci%3ESam%20Bahadur%3C%2Fi%3E%20hits%20most%20of%20its%20targets.%20It%20blends%20the%20story%20of%20an%20illustrious%20life%20-%20it%20isn't%20exactly%20a%20from-the-cradle-to-the-grave%20affair%20although%20it%20does%20begin%20with%20the%20protagonist%20as%20a%20newborn%20in%20a%20crib%20-%20with%20the%20exploits%20of%20a%20legendary%20army%20man%20who%20brought%20remarkable%20dexterity%20to%20bear%20upon%20his%20job%20as%20a%20soldier%20and%20a%20leader.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20screenplay%20by%20Bhavani%20Iyer%2C%20Shantanu%20Srivastava%20and%20Meghna%20Gulzar%20adroitly%20picks%20incidents%20and%20encounters%20that%20aid%20in%20imparting%20a%20vivid%2C%20vibrant%20quality%20to%20the%20picture.%20As%20much%20about%20an%20individual%20as%20about%20a%20nation%2C%20Sam%20Bahadur%20has%20the%20sprawl%20of%20an%20epic%20and%20the%20delicate%20touches%20of%20an%20intimate%20chronicle.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20film%20flits%20from%20one%20point%20in%20time%20to%20another%20from%20the%20early%201940s%20(when%20Japanese%20soldiers%20march%20into%20Burma)%20to%20the%20early%201970s%20(when%20the%20Indian%20Army%20enters%20Bangladesh's%20war%20of%20liberation)%2C%20it%20has%20its%20share%20of%20ellipses.%20But%20no%20matter%20how%20glaring%20the%20gaps%20are%2C%20they%20do%20not%20restrict%20the%20sweep%20of%20the%20consistently%20arresting%20saga.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20screenwriters%20graft%20just%20enough%20narrative%20meat%20on%20to%20the%20condensed%20storyline%20to%20be%20able%20to%20do%20justice%20to%20the%20charismatic%20general%20whose%20career%20it%20explores%20in%20the%20context%20of%20the%20nation's%20eventful%20history%20before%20and%20after%20Independence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20fight%20to%20win%2C%20Manekshaw%20frequently%20asserts%2C%20often%20in%20so%20many%20words.%20That%20might%20make%20him%20sound%20like%20an%20insuperable%20Hindi%20action%20film%20hero.%20But%20the%20director%20makes%20it%20a%20point%20not%20to%20turn%20the%20protagonist%20into%20a%20larger-than-life%20figure%20-%20which%20he%20probably%20was%20to%20the%20men%20he%20led.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKeeping%20hysteria%20out%20of%20history%2C%20she%20presents%20the%20great%20soldier%20not%20as%20a%20single-hued%2C%20punchline-spouting%20general%20but%20as%20a%20believable%20human%20-%20a%20man%20of%20conviction%20-%20intelligent%2C%20confident%20and%20cocky%20-%20and%20a%20master%20strategist%20who%20revelled%20in%20speaking%20his%20mind.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ci%3ESam%20Bahadur%3C%2Fi%3E%20we%20see%20on%20the%20screen%20isn't%20a%20Bollywoodised%20version%20of%20a%20hero%20from%20the%20pages%20of%20Indian%20military%20history%2C%20but%20a%20man%20rooted%20in%20the%20real%20world%20but%20endowed%20with%20exceptional%20acumen%20and%20courage%20of%20conviction.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat's%20in%20a%20name%3F%20In%20the%20case%20of%20Sam%20Manekshaw%2C%20as%20the%20film%20about%20him%20tells%20us%2C%20there%20is%20a%20whole%20lot.%20In%20the%20opening%20sequence%2C%20we%20learn%20that%20Sam's%20parents%20had%20christened%20him%20Cyrus%20but%20were%20constrained%20to%20rename%20him%20because%20a%20thief%20named%20Cyrus%20had%20just%20been%20nabbed%20in%20the%20neighbourhood.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20next%20scene%20-%20it%20is%20repeated%20later%20in%20film%20-%20an%208th%20Gorkha%20Rifles%20jawan%2C%20when%20Manekshaw%20asks%20him%20if%20he%20knows%20the%20name%20of%20the%20Indian%20Army%20chief%2C%20lisps%20%26quot%3BSam%20Bahadur%26quot%3B.%20The%20apt%20moniker%20sticks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPlayed%20with%20panache%20by%20Vicky%20Kaushal%2C%20who%20walks%20the%20tightrope%20between%20caricature%20and%20authenticity%20and%20never%20keels%20over%20on%20to%20the%20side%20of%20the%20former%2C%20Sam%20Manekshaw%20emerges%20as%20a%20man%20and%20an%20icon%20who%20was%20both%20enormously%20charming%20and%20dauntingly%20firm.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFalling%20back%20on%20a%20jaunty%20gait%2C%20dialogue%20delivery%20faintly%20reminiscent%20of%20%3Ci%3EHum%20Dono%3C%2Fi%3E's%20Dev%20Anand%20and%20demeanour%20that%20exudes%20both%20hauteur%20and%20amiability%20-%20Kaushal%20livens%20up%20the%20portraiture%20with%20distinct%20mannerisms%20that%20are%20far%20removed%20from%20his%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20most%20striking%20aspects%20of%20%3Ci%3ESam%20Bahadur%3C%2Fi%3E%20is%20that%20it%20eschews%20flag-waving%20militarism%20while%20celebrating%20the%20bravery%20of%20India's%20soldiers.%20It%20treads%20gently%20and%20thoughtfully%20through%20the%20life-threatening%20minefields%20that%20infantrymen%20have%20to%20negotiate%20in%20the%20line%20of%20duty.%20There%20are%20battle%20scenes%20and%20punchlines%20aplenty%20in%20the%20film%2C%20but%20they%20do%20not%20overshadow%20the%20less%20flashy%20components%20with%20which%20the%20lively%20biopic%20is%20constructed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3ESam%20Bahadur%3C%2Fi%3E%20isn't%20only%20about%20a%20man%20delivering%20rousing%20speeches%20to%20lift%20the%20spirits%20of%20his%20men%20or%20stamp%20his%20personality%20on%20the%20army%20under%20him.%20It%20is%20also%20about%20the%20human%20and%20personal%20aspects%20of%20a%20general's%20life%2C%20which%20are%20underscored%20in%20the%20moments%20that%20he%20has%20with%20his%20wife%20Silloo%20(Sanya%20Malhotra)%20and%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2F6xJptj7AVSA%3Fsi%3DN-SElCA2d9i0vnZK%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20film%20harks%20back%20to%20a%20time%20when%20love%20for%20the%20nation%20was%20not%20coloured%20by%20any%20manner%20of%20religious%20exceptionalism%2C%20it%20showcases%20an%20ethos%20that%20hinged%20on%20a%20celebration%20of%20unity%20in%20diversity%2C%20the%20cornerstone%20of%20the%20idea%20of%20India.%20The%20war%20cries%20of%20the%20various%20regiments%20(in%20the%20film's%20climactic%20passages)%20point%20to%20the%20variegated%20backgrounds%20of%20Indian%20soldiers%20marching%20towards%20a%20common%20goal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20significantly%20resonant%20scene%2C%20a%20court%20of%20inquiry%20charges%20Manekshaw%20with%20being%20anti-national%20because%20the%20defence%20academy%20he%20presides%20over%20has%20portraits%20of%20British%20soldiers%20rather%20than%20those%20of%20Indian%20political%20leaders.%20The%20general's%20response%20to%20the%20flimsy%20allegation%20is%20illuminating.%20The%20academy%20trains%20soldiers%2C%20not%20politicians%2C%20he%20asserts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3ESam%20Bahadur%3C%2Fi%3E%20slips%20up%20a%20bit%20in%20its%20sketchy%20portrayal%20of%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20(played%20by%20Neeraj%20Kabi).%20Indira%20Gandhi%20(Fatima%20Sana%20Shaikh)%20receives%20far%20better%20treatment.%20Not%20only%20does%20India's%20third%20Prime%20Minister%20get%20greater%20play%20in%20the%20narrative%2C%20she%20also%20has%20a%20scene%20or%20two%20is%20which%20she%20nearly%20steals%20Sam's%20thunder.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20one%20sequence%2C%20Mrs%20Gandhi%20puts%20Richard%20Nixon's%20Secretary%20of%20State%20Henry%20Kissinger%20in%20his%20place%20(using%20chief%20of%20army%20staff%20Manekshaw%20as%20her%20trump%20card)%20when%20he%20threatens%20India%20with%20dire%20consequences%20if%20she%20attacks%20Pakistan%20on%20the%20eastern%20front.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENewsreel%20footage%20of%20Sheikh%20Mujibur%20Rahman%20exhorting%20his%20people%20to%20rise%20in%20revolt%2C%20sequences%20of%20Dhaka%20University%20students%20being%20gunned%20down%20by%20the%20Pakistan%20army%20and%20flashes%20of%20General%20Yahya%20Khan%20(Mohammed%20Zeeshan%20Ayyub)%2C%20Manekshaw's%20friend%20in%20their%20pre-Partition%20defence%20academy%20days%2C%20planning%20to%20precipitate%20a%20confrontation%20with%20India%20are%20woven%20into%20the%20lead-up%20to%20the%20Bangladesh%20war.%20So%2C%20Sam%20Bahadur%20isn't%20just%20talk.%20There%20is%20enough%20in%20here%20to%20keep%20the%20film%20on%20the%20boil%20all%20through.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20would%20be%20easy%20to%20describe%20Sam%20Bahadur%20as%20a%20Vicky%20Kaushal%20show%20because%20it%20is%20who%20dominates%20every%20major%20scene%20in%20the%20film.%20But%20without%20the%20fine%20balance%20that%20Meghna%20Gulzar%20strikes%20between%20ambition%20and%20restraint%2C%20neither%20the%20spirited%20central%20performance%20nor%20its%20emotional%20(and%20cinematic)%20payoff%20would%20have%20been%20quite%20as%20remarkable.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701399780000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-12%2F5iv79g5_sam-bahadur_625x300_01_December_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fentertainment%2Fsam-bahadur-review-driven-by-spirited-performance-from-vicky-kaushal-3-5-stars-4623087%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Sam%20Bahadur%20Review%3A%20Without%20the%20fi