20to%20the%20incident%2C%20per%20the%20report.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAn%20alarm%20sounded%2015%20times%20as%20the%20crew%20member%20on%20watch%20was%20recorded%20snoring%2C%20per%20the%20report.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20cargo%20ship%20ran%20aground%20the%20west%20coast%20of%20Scotland%20in%202021%20after%20the%20officer%20on%20watch%20fell%20asleep%20following%20a%20night%20of%20drinking%20with%20his%20fellow%20crew%20members%2C%20a%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fassets.publishing.service.gov.uk%2Fmedia%2F6565cd7b62180b000dce82d0%2F2023-8-BBCMarmara-ReportAndAnnex.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20BBC%20Marmara%2C%20a%20115-meter-long%20cargo%20ship%20owned%20by%20a%20German%20firm%20and%20flying%20under%20a%20Portuguese%20flag%2C%20was%20traveling%20from%20Ireland%20to%20Scotland%20on%20July%2025%2C%202021%2C%20when%20it%20crashed%20into%20the%20island%20of%20Eilean%20Trodday%2C%20according%20to%20a%20new%20investigation%20from%20the%20UK's%20Marine%20Accident%20Investigation%20Branch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%205%2C344-ton%20ship%20was%20eventually%20refloated%20following%20the%20accident%2C%20but%20sustained%20%26quot%3Bsignificant%20damage%26quot%3B%20to%20the%20forward%20part%20of%20its%20hull%2C%20the%20report%20found.%20The%20vessel%2C%20which%20was%20carrying%20concrete%20beams%20on%20board%2C%20was%20forced%20to%20divert%20to%20Poland%20for%20repairs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20recently%20published%20investigation%20criticized%20the%20ship's%20%26quot%3Black%20of%20responsibility%20at%20every%20level%20of%20management%20on%20board%26quot%3B%20and%20said%20the%20ship's%20leadership%20had%20allowed%20alcohol%20abuse%20to%20be%20normalized.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20report%2C%20a%20crew%20member%20learned%20of%20a%20death%20in%20his%20family%20the%20day%20after%20the%20BBC%20Marmara%20left%20port%20in%20July%202021.%20He%20subsequently%20invited%20three%20other%20crew%20members%20back%20to%20his%20cabin%20for%20an%20%26quot%3Binformal%20wake%2C%26quot%3B%20including%20the%20second%20officer%2C%20a%2037-year-old%20Ukrainian%20national.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20crew%20members%20drank%20beer%20and%20J%C3%A4germeister%20in%20the%20man's%20cabin%20for%20about%20three%20hours%2C%20the%20report%20found.%20The%20second%20officer%20then%20left%20to%20take%20over%20the%20watch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShortly%20after%20he%20took%20his%20position%2C%20two%20of%20his%20fellow%20partying%20crew%20members%20came%20to%20join%20him%20on%20the%20vessel's%20bridge%2C%20bringing%20more%20beer%20that%20had%20been%20given%20to%20them%20by%20the%20ship's%20master%2C%20the%20investigation%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20three%20crew%20members%20talked%20and%20played%20music%20for%20about%20an%20hour%20before%20two%20of%20them%20departed%2C%20leaving%20the%20second%20officer%20alone%20around%201%20a.m.%2C%20according%20to%20the%20probe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20an%20hour%20later%2C%20the%20ship%20missed%20a%20planned%20course%20alteration%2C%20triggering%20an%20alarm%20that%20sounded%2015%20times%20before%20the%20route%20was%20effectively%20changed%2C%20the%20report%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20sound%20of%20the%20second%20officer's%20%26quot%3Bloud%20snoring%26quot%3B%20was%20picked%20up%20on%20the%20voyage%20data%20recorder.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAround%203%3A30%20a.m.%2C%20the%20vessel's%20alert%20went%20off%20again%20after%20having%20detected%20a%20coming%20collision%20with%20the%20Scottish%20island%2C%20the%20report%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESoon%20after%2C%20the%20ship%20hit%20land%20at%20a%20speed%20of%2011.2%20knots.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20incident%2C%20the%20ship's%20owners%20and%20managers%20have%20taken%20action%20to%20improve%20the%20company's%20safety%20management%20procedures%2C%20especially%20in%20relation%20to%20the%20use%20of%20alcohol%20on%20board%2C%20the%20investigation%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBriese%20Schiffahrt%2C%20the%20German%20firm