2C%20China%20or%20North%20Korea%20which%20are%20in%20the%20news%20for%20alleged%20crimes%20conducted%20on%20foreign%20soil%2C%20damaging%20their%20reputation.%20Can%20one%20imagine%20how%20India%E2%80%99s%20intel%20and%20information%20sharing%20architecture%20with%20its%20democratic%20allies%20and%20partners%20may%20be%20disrupted%20after%20an%20episode%20like%20this%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20a%20previous%20article%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Findia-g20-economy-world-domestic-outlook%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ethis%20author%20argued%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cspan%3Ehow%20India%E2%80%99s%20paradoxical%20world%20outlook%20and%20waning%20moral%20stature%20in%20conduct%20on%20multilateral%20(and%20some%20bilateral)%20issues%2C%20cannot%20be%20enveloped%20nor%20hidden%20in%20some%20%E2%80%98green%20tented%20sheet%E2%80%99.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20US%20indictment%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ealso%20hints%20at%20what%20may%20have%20informed%20Canadian%20Prime%20Minister%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EJustin%20Trudeau%E2%80%99s%20sensational%20September%202023%20statement%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20there%20were%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9Ccredible%20allegations%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20linking%20the%20Indian%20government%20to%20the%20murder%20of%20another%20Khalistan%20activist.%20While%20Ottawa%20has%20not%20revealed%20much%20in%20public%20%E2%80%93%20apparently%20to%20preserve%20the%20confidentiality%20of%20judicial%20proceedings%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fnijjar-pannun-modi-foreign-policy-national-interest%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ea%20piece%20published%20by%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20says%20it%20is%20clear%20that%20%E2%80%9CCanadian%20officials%20had%20the%20Pannun%20case%20in%20mind%20and%20that%20at%20least%20some%20part%20of%20the%20intelligence%20linking%20India%20to%20Nijjar%20has%20come%20in%20the%20form%20of%20electronic%20messages%20the%20US%20has%20captured%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F30010249%2Findictment.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F30010249%2Findictment.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F30010249%2Findictment-300x150.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F30010249%2Findictment-1024x512.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F30010249%2Findictment-800x400.jpg%20800w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-687016%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EGurpatwant%20Singh%20Pannun%2C%20a%20still%20image%20ofthe%20Advance%20Payment%20as%20shown%20in%20the%20DoJ%20indictment%20of%20Nikhil%20Gupta%2C%20and%20Hardeep%20Singh%20Nijjar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20have%20now%20seen%20at%20least%20two%20instances%20of%20charges%20by%20India%E2%80%99s%20democratic%20allies%20and%20partners%20of%20not%20being%20%E2%80%98honest%E2%80%99%20or%20%E2%80%98truthful%E2%80%99%20to%20its%20global%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Emoral%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Estanding.%20In%20India%E2%80%99s%20own%20amoral%2C%20apathetic%20exceptionalism%2C%20there%20is%20also%20a%20silent%20embrace%20of%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20assassin%20Nathuram%20Godse%2C%20and%20his%20(Godse%E2%80%99s)%20ideological%20disposition%2C%20as%20against%20an%20embrace%20of%20Gandhian%20ideals%20of%20peace%20and%20non-violence%20which%20made%20India%20globally%20recognised%20and%20respected%20by%20all%20powers%20across%20the%20globe.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20also%20buffoonish%20for%20India%E2%80%99s%20foreign%20policy%20ecosystem%20to%20believe%20it%20enjoys%20an%20undistilled%20faith%20amongst%20the%20(still)%20powerful%20G7%20countries%20if%20the%20tools%20for%20channelising%20instruments%20of%20economic%20integration%20operate%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Esans%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20the%20basic%20domestic%20prerequisites%20of%20realised%20social%20cohesion%3B%20a%20safeguarded%20rights-based%20constitutional%20order%2C%20ensured%20by%20the%20separation%20of%20powers.%20India%20can%20hardly%20compromise%20on%20these%20prerequisites%20if%20it%20is%20serious%20about%20playing%20a%20more%20important%20role%20in%20a%20complex%2C%20multi-polar%20world.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fnijjar-pannun-modi-foreign-policy-national-interest%5C%22%3EFrom%20Nijjar%20to%20Pannun%2C%20Modi%20Government%E2%80%99s%20Recklessness%20is%20Undermining%20National%20Interest%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20West%E2%80%99s%20more%20accommodative%20position%20on%20a%20number%20of%20contested%20issues%20%E2%80%93%20India%E2%80%99s%20position%20on%20the%20Israel-Palestine%20conflict%2C%20the%20Ukraine-Russia%20war%2C%20or%20on%20domestic%20issues%20like%20human%20rights%2C%20minority%20protection%2C%20and%20freedom%20of%20press%20%E2%80%93%20is%20rather%20explained%20by%20their%20greater%20contempt%20for%20an%20authoritarian%20China%20under%20Xi%20Jinping%2C%20than%20say%2C%20a%20need%20for%20developing%20bonhomie%20with%20India.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EModi%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ENew%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%20%E2%80%93%20amidst%20a%20rising%2C%20ideological%20wave%20of%20Hindutva%20%E2%80%93%20embraces%20Godse%E2%80%99s%20violence%20and%20an%20eye%20for%20an%20eye%20vengeance-seeking%20mindset.%20This%20has%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dailyo.in%2Fvariety%2Fgeorge-floyd-breonna-taylor-racism-in-usa-anti-caa-nrc-protests-social-justice-polarisation-33154%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Enothing%20to%20do%20with%20social%20justice%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EJustice%20isn%E2%80%99t%20about%20seeking%20vengeance%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20or%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Erevenge%20%E2%80%93%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thequint.com%2Fopinion%2Fisrael-palestine-need-for-transcendental-justice-in-a-world-marred-by-conflict-conquest%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eit%20is%20much%20more%20than%20that%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEmbracing%20violence%20and%20violent%20means%20of%20institutional%20propriety%2C%20and%20an%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thequint.com%2Fopinion%2Fisrael-palestine-need-for-transcendental-justice-in-a-world-marred-by-conflict-conquest%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eapathetic%20conduct%20towards%20peace%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20own%20domestic%20and%20subsequently%20international%20position%2C%20may%2C%20unfortunately%2C%20make%20the%20nation%E2%80%99s%20image%20regress%2C%20or%20fall%20into%20the%20same%20category%20of%20authoritarian%20nation-states%20(or%20%E2%80%98illiberal%20democracies%E2%80%99).%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECollective%20self-interest%20is%20difficult%20to%20realise%20by%20an%20independently%20motivated%20self-interested%20state%20of%20individuals%20unless%20each%20state%20has%20some%20form%20of%20assurance%20that%20others%20will%20conform%20if%20it%20does.%20And%20that%20assurance%20requires%20the%20external%20incentive%20provided%20by%20the%20sovereign%2C%20who%20sees%20to%20it%20that%20individual%20and%20collective%20self-interest%20coincide.%20It%20is%20critical%20for%20any%20nation%20(including%20India)%20to%20realise%20this.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Findias-abstention-in-un-gaza-truce-vote-reflects-amoral-apathetic-exceptionalism%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%98s%20founding%20editor%20argued%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20security%20history%20has%20been%20known%20to%20arm%20and%20train%20the%20Liberation%20Tigers%20of%20Tamil%20Eelam%20in%20Sri%20Lanka%3B%20and%20launching%20%E2%80%98surgical%20strikes%E2%80%99%20on%20alleged%20terrorist%20sites%20inside%20Pakistan-controlled%20territory.%20But%2C%20India%20has%20never%20so%20far%20been%20associated%20with%20targeted%20assassinations%20abroad.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ENew%20Delhi%20has%20shown%20no%20appetite%20for%20physically%20targeting%20wanted%20men%20or%20opponents%20overseas%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Enot%20necessarily%20beacuse%20of%20the%20lack%20of%20capability%20but%20a%20realistic%20political%20calculation%20about%20the%20associated%20risks%20and%20benefits.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhat%20the%20current%20US%20indictment%20and%20the%20recklessness%20with%20which%20India%20responded%20to%20Trudeau%E2%80%99s%20allegations%20have%20done%20is%20put%20not%20just%20the%20current%20government%20but%20India%E2%80%99s%20own%20image%20and%20global%20position%20in%20the%20international%20security%20arena%2C%20in%20a%20more%20vulnerable%20position.%20It%20may%20cause%20more%20distance%20to%20be%20observed%20by%20democratic%20allies.%20Preferring%20Godse%20over%20Gandhi%20has%20a%20cost%2C%20not%20just%20in%20terms%20of%20an%20ideological%2C%20political%20disposition%2C%20but%20also%20from%20the%20perspective%20of%20foreign%20policy%20and%20how%20the%20world%20perceives%20the%20country%20in%20the%20near%20(and%20far%20future).%20Any%20Indian%20government%20and%20its%20leadership%20would%20be%20wise%20to%20recognise%20this.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fdeepanshu-mohan%5C%22%3EDeepanshu%20Mohan%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20associate%20professor%20of%20economics%20and%20director%2C%20Centre%20for%20New%20Economics%20Studies%2C%20Jindal%20School%20of%20Liberal%20Arts%20and%20Humanities%2C%20O.P.%20Jindal%20Global%20University.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701358187000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F30204640%2Fmodi-doval-jaishankar.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Findia-godse-violence-gandhi-peace-global-image-khalistan-activists%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Modi%E2%80%99s%20New%20India%20%E2%80%93%20amidst%20a%20rising%2C%20ideological%20wave%20of%20Hindutva%20%E2%80%93%20embraces%20Godse%E2%80%99s%20violence%20and%20an%20eye%20for%20an%20eye%20vengeance-seeking%20mindset.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Findia-godse-violence-gandhi-peace-global-image-khalistan-activists%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Go%20First%20CEO%20Kaushik%20Khona%20resigns%20amid%20airline's%20uncertain%20future%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701357339000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2022-07%2F19%2Ffull%2F1658243055-3588.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fgo-first-ceo-kaushik-khona-resigns-amid-airline-s-uncertain-future-123113001094_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Go%20First%20stopped%20flying%20in%20early%20May%20and%20filed%20for%20voluntary%20bankruptcy%20proceedings%20amid%20financial%20woes%2C%20mainly%20triggered%20by%20Pratt%20%26amp%3B%20Whitney%20engine%20issues%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fgo-first-ceo-kaushik-khona-resigns-amid-airline-s-uncertain-future-123113001094_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fgo-first-ceo-kaushik-khona-resigns-amid-airline-s-uncertain-future-123113001094_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fgo-first-ceo-kaushik-khona-resigns-amid-airline-s-uncertain-future-123113001094_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Elon%20Musk%3A%20A%20timeline%20of%20his%20most%20recent%20controversial%20moments%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701357180000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F07%2F70x70%2Fskynews-elon-musk-ai_6217043.jpg%3F20230712213547%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Felon-musk-what-are-his-most-recent-controversial-moments-13019651%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Elon%20Musk%20has%20apologised%20for%20endorsing%20an%20antisemitic%20conspiracy%20theory%2C%20admitting%20it%20may%20have%20been%20%26quot%3Bliterally%20the%20worst%20and%20dumbest%20post%20I've%20ever%20done%26quot%3B.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A323%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Felon-musk-what-are-his-most-recent-controversial-moments-13019651%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Felon-musk-what-are-his-most-recent-controversial-moments-13019651%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Felon-musk-what-are-his-most-recent-controversial-moments-13019651%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Haritha%20Haaram%3A%20How%20Telangana's%20Afforestation%20Project%20Proved%20Detrimental%20to%20Adivasi%20Rights%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F30195518%2FEffect-6.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20electioneering%20in%20Telangana%2C%20several%20issues%20of%20welfare%2C%20development%2C%20and%20various%20demographic%20groups%20came%20to%20the%20fore.%20However%2C%20Haritha%20Haaram%2C%20a%20pet%20project%20of%20the%20Bharat%20Rashtra%20Samithi%20(BRS)%20government%2C%20did%20not%20garner%20much%20attention.%20The%20stated%20objective%20of%20the%20initiative%20is%20to%20promote%20afforestation%20across%20the%20state.%20The%20initiative%20helps%20us%20understand%20the%20intersection%20of%20environmental%20politics%2C%20marginalisation%20of%20Adivasis%2C%20and%20the%20continued%20reliance%20on%20outdated%2C%20unscientific%2C%20and%20colonial%20conservation%20practices%20followed%20by%20the%20forest%20bureaucracy%20in%20Telangana.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHaritha%20Haaram%3A%20Boon%20or%20bane%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHaritha%20Haaram%2C%20which%20was%20rolled%20out%20in%202014%2C%20is%20a%20state-wide%20plantation%20programme%20for%20planting%20seedlings%20to%20increase%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20forest%20cover%20to%2033%25%20from%2024%25.%20With%20a%20massive%20investment%20of%20Rs%208%2C511%20crore%2C%20as%20per%20December%202022%20estimates%2C%20the%20BRS%20government%20claims%20to%20have%20planted%20around%20266%20crore%20saplings%2C%20surpassing%20the%20target%20of%20230%20crore%20saplings%20originally%20envisioned%20as%20part%20of%20the%20programme.%20It%20is%2C%20however%2C%20unclear%20how%20many%20of%20these%20saplings%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thenewsminute.com%2Ftelangana%2Fharitha-haram-266-cr-saplings-planted-8-yrs-telangana-how-many-survived-170925%5C%22%3Esurvived%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMultiple%20afforestation%20efforts%20have%20been%20on%20inside%20the%20forested%20areas%20and%20in%20non-forested%20areas%2C%20which%20include%20grasslands%2C%20wasteland%2C%20and%20community%20commons.%20According%20to%20officials%2C%2090%25%20of%20the%20seedlings%20survived%20inside%20the%20forested%20zones%2C%20whereas%20the%20success%20rate%20is%2070%25-80%25%20for%20the%20plantations%20outside%20of%20forested%20areas.%20This%20is%20not%20verified%20by%20any%20independent%20auditor%20or%20scientific%20study%2C%20yet%20the%20NITI%20Aayog%20has%20endorsed%20and%20encouraged%20Haritha%20Haaram%20after%20eight%20years%20of%20its%20supposed%20%E2%80%98success%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20Telangana%20is%20among%20the%20top%20states%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftelanganatoday.com%2Fover-3-lakh-hectares-of-forest-land-diverted-under-forest-conservation-act-in-15-years-govt%5C%22%3Edivert%20forest%20lands%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20non-forestry%20activities.%20According%20to%20the%20data%20from%20the%20Union%20Environment%20Ministry%2C%20Telangana%20diverted%2019%2C419%20hectares%20of%20forest%20land%20over%20the%20last%2015%20years%20under%20the%20Forest%20(Conservation)%20Act%2C%201980.%20Here%20is%20the%20contradiction%2C%20on%20the%20one%20hand%2C%20the%20issue%20of%20rapidly%20depleting%20natural%20forests%20for%20non-forestry%20purposes%2C%20and%20on%20the%20other%2C%20parallel%20afforestation%20programmes%20underway%2C%20which%20are%20aligned%20with%20the%20Compensatory%20Afforestation%20Fund%20Management%20Authority%20(CAMPA).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Facademic.oup.com%2Fbioscience%2Farticle%2F70%2F11%2F947%2F5903754%3Flogin%3Dtrue%26s%3D09%5C%22%3EVarious%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ecologyandsociety.org%2Fvol25%2Fiss4%2Fart1%2F%5C%22%3Eresearch%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fassets.researchsquare.com%2Ffiles%2Frs-289460%2Fv1_covered.pdf%3Fc%3D1637595601%5C%22%3Edemonstrated%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS0305750X22000547%5C%22%3Eproblems%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20such%20contradictory%20policies.%20Increasingly%2C%20studies%20in%20India%20and%20elsewhere%20have%20argued%20about%20the%20limitations%20of%20afforestation%20in%20certain%20landscapes.%20Replacing%20natural%20forests%20is%20not%20the%20one-size-fits-all%20solution%20for%20climate%20change%20mitigation%20strategy%2C%20for%20it%20harms%20local%20ecology%2C%20and%20dispossesses%20pastoral%20and%20indigenous%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20this%20article%20will%20not%20dwell%20on%20the%20scientific%20unviability%20of%20these%20programmes%2C%20nor%20the%20claims%20of%20Haritha%20Haaram%20being%20%E2%80%98successful%E2%80%99.%20It%20is%20concerned%20with%20the%20plight%20of%20small-scale%20farmers%20and%20Adivasis%20who%20have%20been%20displaced%20due%20to%20the%20plantation%20programme.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EForest%20Rights%20Act%2C%202006%20and%20Settlement%20of%20Rights%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Forest%20Right%20Act%202006%20is%20a%20landmark%20legislation%20enacted%20to%20correct%20historical%20injustices%20meted%20upon%20the%20Adivasi%2C%20forest-dwelling%2C%20and%20pastoral%20communities%20during%20the%20colonial%20period%20as%20well%20as%20in%20the%20post-independent%20era.%20The%20Preamble%20of%20the%20Act%20states%20that%20historical%20injustices%20must%20be%20addressed.%20The%20Act%20ensures%20recognition%20of%20community%20rights%20and%20livelihood%20security%20for%20the%20Adivasis%20or%20the%20Scheduled%20Tribes%20(ST)%20and%20Other%20Forest-Dwelling%20(OTFD)%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F07%2F10143411%2FInto-the-forest-scenery-Gorumara-forest-India-86509-pixahive-1024x631-1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F07%2F10143411%2FInto-the-forest-scenery-Gorumara-forest-India-86509-pixahive-1024x631-1.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F07%2F10143411%2FInto-the-forest-scenery-Gorumara-forest-India-86509-pixahive-1024x631-1-300x185.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-606748%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22631%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPhoto%3A%20Roy%2FPixahive%2C%20CC0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdivasis%20consist%20of%209.3%25%20of%20the%20total%20population%20in%20Telangana%20(Census%202011).%20Some%20of%20the%20major%20tribal%20communities%20in%20Telangana%20include%20the%20Lambada%2C%20Gond%2C%20Kolam%2C%20Thoti%2C%20Pardhan%2C%20Mannewar%2C%20Nayakpod%2C%20Koya%2C%20Kondareddy%2C%20Chenchu%2C%20Nakkala%2C%20Yerukala%2C%20Yanadi%2C%20among%20others.%20Pastoral%20communities%20like%20Kurumbas%20and%20Gola%20Kurumbs%20are%20also%20part%20of%20the%20ST%20communities.%20Most%20of%20the%20forest%20areas%20of%20Telangana%20are%20located%20in%20the%20erstwhile%20undivided%20districts%20of%20Khammam%2C%20Warangal%2C%20Adilabad%2C%20and%20Mahabubnagar.%20The%20total%20forest%20area%20in%20Telangana%20is%20around%2063.50%20lakh%20acres%20(26%2C904%20sq.%20km).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20few%20years%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanchronicle.com%2Fnation%2Fcurrent-affairs%2F010719%2Ftrs-activists-beat-up-woman-forest-officers-staff-with-sticks-poles.html%5C%22%3Emultiple%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newsclick.in%2FTelangana-Tribals-Resist-Haritha-Haram-Podu-Lands%5C%22%3Emedia%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheprint.in%2Findia%2Fwhy-telangana-is-seeing-an-increase-in-violent-clashes-between-tribals-forest-officials%2F731548%2F%5C%22%3Ereports%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20shown%20the%20violent%20side%20of%20the%20Haritha%20Haaram%20programme%2C%20which%20involves%20the%20plantation%20of%20saplings%20as%20well%20as%20the%20large-scale%20digging%20of%20trenches%20around%20Adivasi%20habitations.%20This%20implies%20the%20denial%20of%20access%20to%20forest%20lands%20for%20those%20who%20are%20dependent%20on%20the%20same%20for%20farming%20or%20grazing%20purposes%2C%20conflicting%20with%20the%20spirit%20of%20the%20FRA.%20The%20provisions%20of%20FRA%20clearly%20state%20that%20eviction%20of%20forest%20dwellers%20without%20settlement%20of%20rights%20is%20a%20violation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Ftelangana-forest-officer-killing-podu-cultivation%5C%22%3ETelangana%3A%20Forest%20Officer%E2%80%99s%20Killing%20Brings%20to%20Fore%20Issue%20of%20Podu%20Cultivation%20Again%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20districts%20of%20Bhadradri%20Kothagudem%2C%20Mancherial%2C%20Warangal%2C%20Adilabad%2C%20and%20Asifabad%2C%20the%20forest%20department%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thenewsminute.com%2Ftelangana%2Fpodu-land-controversy-telangana-adivasis-call-bandh-july-11-165671%5C%22%3Eforcibly%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newsclick.in%2FTussle-Between-Farmers-Forest-Officials-Telangana%5C%22%3Eevicting%3C%2Fa%3E%20tribal%20households%20engaged%20in%20%3Cem%3Epodu%3C%2Fem%3E%20cultivation%20(a%20traditional%20form%20of%20shifting%20cultivation)%20on%20forest%20lands.%20The%20department%20has%20been%20accused%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thenewsminute.com%2Ftelangana%2Fharassment-over-podu-land-issue-adivasi-advocates-demand-national-intervention-165768%5C%22%3Ebooking%20false%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%3E%20cases%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20in%20several%20villages%20because%20those%20tribals%20do%20not%20possess%20Recognition%20of%20Forest%20Rights%20pattas%20for%20those%20lands.%20While%20the%20plantation%20drive%20using%20Compensatory%20Afforestation%20Fund%20Management%20Authority%20(CAMPA)%20and%20other%20funds%20dilutes%20the%20key%20provisions%20of%20the%20FRA%20and%20Panchayat%20Extension%20to%20Scheduled%20Areas%20Act%20(PESA%20Act)%2C%20it%20also%20comes%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20denudation%20of%20natural%2C%20biodiverse%20forests%2C%20and%20its%20replacement%20with%20monoculture%20plantations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHabitat%20rights%20of%20the%20Particularly%20Vulnerable%20Tribal%20Groups%20(PVTGs)%20have%20also%20not%20been%20recognised%20under%20the%20FRA%20in%20Telangana.%20Under%20the%20amended%20FRA%20Rules%2C%202012%2C%20the%20District%20Level%20Committee%20(DLC)%20chaired%20by%20the%20district%20collector%2C%20is%20mandated%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20habitat%20rights%20of%20PVTGs%20are%20recognised.%20Such%20PVTG%20communities%20have%20also%20been%20facing%20the%20threat%20of%20eviction%20from%20their%20habitats%20for%20Tiger%20Reserve%20projects%20in%20Kawal%20and%20Amrabad%20Tiger%20Reserve.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20hardly%20any%20records%20or%20reports%20of%20recognition%20of%20Community%20Rights%20(CR%2FCFR)%20and%20Habitat%20Rights%20for%20PVTG%20communities%20and%20other%20ST%20communities%20in%20National%20Parks%20and%20Protected%20Areas.%20There%20is%20also%20a%20lack%20of%20communication%20on%20rejected%20FRA%20claims%20and%20why%20fresh%20claims%20have%20not%20been%20accepted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAn%20inconvenient%20flashback%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F30194017%2FTelangana-FRA-Implementation-2018-2023.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F30194017%2FTelangana-FRA-Implementation-2018-2023.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F30194017%2FTelangana-FRA-Implementation-2018-2023-300x116.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F30194017%2FTelangana-FRA-Implementation-2018-2023-1024x394.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-687147%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22462%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESource%3A%C2%A0%20Ministry%20of%20Tribal%20Affairs.%20Monthly%20Progress%20Report%3A%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftribal.nic.in%2FFRA.aspx%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ehttps%3A%2F%2Ftribal.nic.in%2FFRA.aspx%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cem%3E(June%202023)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20above%20table%20shows%20the%20progress%20in%20the%20last%20five%20years%20in%20FRA%20implementation%20in%20Telangana%2C%20which%20can%20be%20summed%20up%20as%20dismal%20and%20negligent.%20Of%20the%2020%2C305%20odd%20claims%20under%20the%20category%20of%20individual%20forest%20rights%20(IFR)%20and%20community%20forest%20rights%20(CFR)%20since%20March%202018%2C%20only%203%2C176%20titles%20have%20been%20approved%2C%20which%20is%20only%2015%25%20of%20the%20claims.%20As%20many%20as%2010%2C669%20or%2051%25%20of%20claims%20have%20been%20rejected.%20There%20were%202%2C808%20community%20rights%20title%20claims%20filed%20as%20of%20June%202023%2C%20and%20only%20102%20were%20recognised.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20is%20worrying%20is%20that%20as%20of%20June%202023%2C%20overall%2092.7%25%20of%20the%20claims%20were%20disposed%20of%20with%20respect%20to%20claims%20received%2C%20whereas%20only%2047%25%20of%20the%20total%20claims%20were%20approved.%20As%20many%20as%2094%2C426%20claims%20were%20rejected%2C%20and%20little%20has%20been%20done%20so%20far%20to%20convey%20the%20reasons%20for%20the%20rejections%20of%20claims%20to%20the%20claimants.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thenewsminute.com%2Ftelangana%2Fharassment-over-podu-land-issue-adivasi-advocates-demand-national-intervention-165768%5C%22%3EReports%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20also%20suggested%20that%20rejection%20is%20often%20based%20on%20frivolous%20grounds%2C%20completely%20in%20violation%20of%20the%20FRA%2C%202006%2C%20which%20clearly%20states%20that%20detailed%20reasons%20must%20be%20provided%20for%20rejection%20of%20claims.%20Based%20on%20the%20data%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frightsandresources.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F11%2FIndia-Promise-and-Performance-National-Report_CFRLA_2016.pdf%5C%22%3ECFR%20%E2%80%93%20LA%20Report%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%202016%20on%20the%20potential%20of%20the%20Forest%20Rights%20Act%20%26amp%3B%20Community%20Forest%20Rights%20in%20India%2C%20it%20was%20found%20that%20Telangana%20has%20almost%2040%20lakh%20acres%20of%20forest%20land%20which%20has%20the%20potential%20for%20recognition%20under%20the%20FRA%2C%202006%20of%20various%20communities%2C%20including%20both%20ST%20and%20OTFD.%20More%20than%2010%20million%20people%2C%20which%20includes%20STs%2C%20pastoralist%20communities%2C%20and%20OTFDs%20may%20benefit%20from%20the%20provisions%20of%20FRA%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20framing%20PESA%20rules%20in%202011%20and%20adopted%20after%20reorganisation%20of%20the%20separate%20state%20in%202014%2C%20there%20has%20practically%20been%20no%20implementation%20of%20PESA%20provisions%20in%20Telangana.%20The%20failure%20to%20constitute%20habitation-level%20Gram%20Sabhas%2C%20and%20strengthen%20the%20same%2C%20has%20resulted%20in%20the%20poor%20implementation%20of%20FRA%20across%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20the%20primacy%20of%20Gram%20Sabha%20consent%20is%20being%20completely%20bypassed%20in%20the%20formulation%20or%20implementation%20of%20key%20decisions%20related%20to%20land%20acquisition%20for%20public%20purpose%20projects%2C%20use%20of%20Compensatory%20Afforestation%20Fund%20Management%20Authority%20(CAMPA)%20funds%20for%20afforestation%20schemes%20%E2%80%93%20such%20as%20Harita%20Haaram%20or%20even%20selection%20of%20beneficiaries%20for%20housing%20schemes%20under%20the%20recently%20announced%20Gruha%20Lakshmi%20scheme%2C%20etc.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAfforestation%20with%20FRA%2C%202006%20%E2%80%93%20The%20way%20forward%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20afforestation%20schemes%20by%20the%20Telangana%20government%2C%20despite%20their%20perceived%20%E2%80%98success%E2%80%99%2C%20find%20little%20or%20no%20place%20in%20the%20electoral%20discourse%20of%20the%20ruling%20party.%20After%20all%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20important%20to%20recognise%20that%20politics%20is%20not%20always%20about%20what%20is%20being%20said%2C%20but%20it%20is%20often%20about%20what%20is%20not%20being%20said.%20Many%20Adivasi%20families%20have%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thenewsminute.com%2Ftelangana%2Ftelangana-govt-stalls-podu-land-scrutiny-nearly-one-lakh-adivasis-hit-162756%5C%22%3Edisplaced%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20those%20who%20have%20resisted%20face%20cases%20against%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20few%20months%20before%20the%20elections%2C%20chief%20minister%20K.%20Chandrashekar%20Rao%20said%20that%20some%20cases%20would%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fhyderabad%2Fpodu-govt-to-withdraw-cases-against-tribals%2Farticleshow%2F101406314.cms%5C%22%3Ewithdrawn%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20however%2C%20the%20indignity%20that%20ensued%20in%20the%20process%20might%20have%20damaged%20the%20ruling%20party%E2%80%99s%20electoral%20prospects%20among%20Adivasis%20and%20marginal%20cultivators%20in%20predominantly%20Adivasi%20districts%20and%20constituencies.%20That%20is%20perhaps%20the%20reason%20behind%20the%20ruling%20party%E2%80%99s%20silence%20on%20its%20flagship%20afforestation%20project.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20afforestation%20programme%20has%20extraordinary%20ambitions.%20However%2C%20the%20programme%20can%20only%20be%20successful%20by%20including%20and%20consulting%20various%20communities.%20Existing%20laws%20like%20PESA%20and%20FRA%20offer%20relevant%20solutions%20to%20prevent%20governments%20from%20falling%20into%20the%20trap%20of%20an%20exclusionary%20model%20of%20conservation%2C%20which%20undermines%20the%20rights%20of%20the%20Adivasis%20and%20other%20forest-dependent%20communities.%20Recognition%20of%20forest%20rights%20%E2%80%93%20both%20individual%20and%20community%20%E2%80%93%20is%20central%20to%20the%20integrity%20of%20our%20ecological%20and%20social%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEnvironmental%20concerns%20cannot%20isolate%20the%20issues%20of%20the%20Adivasis%20and%20the%20recognition%20of%20forest-dependent%20communities.%20The%20electoral%20value%20of%20these%20issues%20cannot%20be%20undermined%2C%20and%20political%20parties%20must%20speak%20up%20on%20these%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E*619%20Community%20Rights%20titles%20were%20cancelled%20on%20the%20grounds%20of%20violating%20the%20FRA.%20These%20Community%20Forest%20Rights%20(CFR)%20titles%20have%20been%20granted%20to%20the%20Vana%20Samrakshana%20Samitis%20(VSS)%20which%20are%20under%20the%20control%20of%20the%20forest%20department%20and%20are%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20not%20covered%20under%20the%20term%20%E2%80%98forest%20dwelling%20Scheduled%20tribes%20and%20other%20traditional%20forest%20dwellers%E2%80%9D%20as%20given%20in%20Sections%202(c)%20and%202(o)%20of%20the%20Forest%20Rights%20Act%20and%20therefore%20these%20committees%20cannot%20be%20considered%20as%20claimants%20for%20granting%20community%20forest%20Rights.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E**102%20titles%20are%20still%20recognised%20as%20Community%20Rights%2FCFR%20titles%3B%20however%2C%20the%20details%20of%20the%20nature%20of%20these%20rights%20remain%20elusive.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cem%3E%3Cbr%3E%5CnAzam%20Danish%20is%20an%20independent%20researcher.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701356440000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F30195518%2FEffect-6.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fharitha-haaram-how-telanganas-afforestation-project-proved-detrimental-to-adivasi-rights%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22On%20the%20flip%20side%20of%20the%20positive%20perception%20it%20garners%2C%20the%20BRS%20government's%20afforestation%20programme%20has%20been%20accused%20of%20denying%20access%20to%20forest%20lands%20for%20those%20who%20are%20dependent%20on%20them%20for%20farming%20or%20grazing%20purposes%2C%20conflicting%20with%20the%20spirit%20of%20the%20Forest%20Rights%20Act.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fharitha-haaram-how-telanganas-afforestation-project-proved-detrimental-to-adivasi-rights%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22In%20Democratic%20India%2C%20Why%20Was%20Statue%20of%20Manu%20Installed%20in%20a%20Court%20Before%20Ambedkar%E2%80%99s%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F08%2F16155753%2FManu-Rajasthan-HC.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20November%2026%2C%202023%2C%20a%20nine-foot-tall%20statue%20of%20B.R.%20Ambedkar%20was%20installed%20in%20the%20premises%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%20on%20the%20occasion%20of%20Constitution%20Day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIronically%2C%20the%20architect%20of%20the%20Indian%20constitution%20had%20to%20wait%20for%2075%20years%20after%20independence%20for%20a%20statue%20to%20be%20erected%20in%20his%20honour.%20All%20this%20while%2C%20a%20taller%20statue%20of%20Manu%20(11%20feet)%20%E2%80%93%20whose%20teachings%20are%20against%20the%20basic%20structure%20and%20values%20of%20the%20constitution%20%E2%80%93%20was%20unveiled%20on%20the%20premises%20of%20the%20Jaipur%20bench%20of%20the%20Rajasthan%20high%20court%20way%20back%20in%201989.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%201970s%2C%20veteran%20Ambedkarite%20leader%20Dadasaheb%20Gaikwad%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.themooknayak.com%2Findia%2Fconstitution-month-special-dr-ambedkars-statue-to-grace-supreme-court-after-76-years-of-independence%5C%22%3Estarted%20his%20efforts%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20push%20for%20the%20installation%20of%20Ambedkar%E2%80%99s%20statue%20within%20the%20parliament%20complex.%20It%20was%20given%20heed%20only%20after%2056%20years.%20In%20contrast%2C%20it%20took%20hardly%2023%20days%20to%20install%20Manu%E2%80%99s%20statue%20in%20the%20Rajasthan%20high%20court%2C%20similar%20to%20the%20implementation%20of%20reservation%20for%20the%20Economically%20Weaker%20Sections%20(EWS)%20among%20the%20upper%20castes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20prompt%20installation%20of%20the%20statue%20of%20Manu%20and%20the%20reluctance%20towards%20Ambedkar%20can%20be%20seen%20as%20a%20metaphor%20for%20the%20polity%20and%20society%20of%20post-independent%20India%2C%20which%20seems%20to%20show%20a%20continuity%20rather%20than%20a%20rupture%20after%201947.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20story%20of%20the%20existence%20of%20Manu%E2%80%99s%20statue%20can%20be%20seen%20as%20a%20glorification%20of%20undemocratic%20and%20oppressive%20Brahmanical%20values%2C%20sustaining%20all%20weathers%2C%20institutions%2C%20and%20governments%20of%20democratic%20India%2C%20which%20is%20slowly%20substituting%20Ambedkar%20from%20within.%20This%20is%20also%20a%20story%20of%20the%20victory%20of%20Manu%E2%80%99s%20India%20over%20the%20vision%20Ambedkar%20aspired%20for%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F30182411%2Fimage-1559.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221006%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F30182411%2Fimage-1559.png%201006w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F30182411%2Fimage-1559-300x243.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-687134%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22815%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EB.R.%20Ambedkar%E2%80%99s%20statue%20in%20the%20premises%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India.%20Photo%3A%20X%40ambedkariteIND%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EManu%E2%80%99s%20Bar%20and%20Bench%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20February%2010%2C%201989%2C%20Padam%20Kumar%20Jain%2C%20the%20president%20of%20the%20Rajasthan%20High%20Court%20Officers%E2%80%99%20Association%2C%20proposed%20installing%20Manu%E2%80%99s%20statue%20in%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20premises%20as%20part%20of%20a%20%E2%80%9Cbeautification%20plan%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20beautification%20was%20the%20goal%2C%20why%20didn%E2%80%99t%20Jain%20consider%20an%20Ambedkar%20statue%2C%20is%20an%20irrelevant%20question.%20Immediately%2C%20just%2023%20days%20after%20this%20proposal%2C%20on%20March%203%2C%201989%2C%20the%20proposal%20was%20approved.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20that%20time%2C%20Shiv%20Charan%20Mathur%20of%20the%20Congress%20was%20the%20chief%20minister%20of%20Rajasthan%3B%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20was%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20and%20Justice%20E.S.%20Venkataramiah%20was%20the%20chief%20justice%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhy%20didn%E2%80%99t%20this%20move%20seem%20objectionable%20to%20any%20of%20them%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20opposition%20to%20the%20installation%20of%20Manu%E2%80%99s%20statue%20%E2%80%93%20which%20was%20considered%20a%20stain%20on%20the%20dignity%20and%20values%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20Dalits%2C%20women%2C%20Shudras%20and%20working%20classes%20%E2%80%93%20the%20awakened%20Dalit%20community%20slowly%20began%20to%20protest.%20Hence%2C%20on%20July%2028%2C%201989%2C%20a%20full%20court%20sitting%20of%20the%20Rajasthan%20high%20court%20unanimously%20decided%20to%20remove%20the%20statue.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20immediately%2C%20Acharya%20Dharmendra%2C%20a%20leader%20of%20the%20Vishwa%20Hindu%20Parishad%20(VHP)%2C%20filed%20a%20public%20interest%20litigation%20(PIL)%20against%20it.%20The%20high%20court%20quickly%20accepted%20this%20PIL%20for%20hearing%2C%20and%20in%20August%201989%2C%20a%20stay%20order%20was%20issued%20against%20its%20own%20full%20sitting.%20Not%20only%20that%2C%20it%20also%20instructed%20that%20any%20further%20hearings%20in%20this%20case%20should%20be%20conducted%20only%20by%20a%20division%20bench%2C%20including%20the%20chief%20justice%20of%20the%20high%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20then%2C%20the%20stay%20order%20and%20Manu%E2%80%99s%20statue%20have%20remained%20on%20the%20premises%20of%20the%20high%20court.%20And%20the%20case%20itself%20has%20acquired%20the%20notoriety%20of%20the%20longest%20pending%20PIL%20in%20the%20history%20of%20the%20Rajasthan%20high%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20recent%20hearing%20on%20this%20case%20happened%20in%202015.%20Over%20300%20Brahmin%20and%20%E2%80%98upper%E2%80%99%20caste%20lawyers%20had%20rushed%20from%20various%20courts%20to%20attend%20the%20hearing.%20As%20A.K.%20Jain%2C%20an%20advocate%20for%20the%20Dalit%20groups%2C%20tried%20to%20draw%20the%20judges%E2%80%99%20attention%20to%20the%20anti-Dalit%2C%20Shudra%20and%20women%20verses%20in%20Manusmriti%2C%20these%20%E2%80%98upper%E2%80%99%20caste%20lawyers%20started%20a%20commotion%20inside%20the%20court%20premises%2C%20leading%20to%20the%20postponement%20of%20the%20hearing.%20It%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.outlookindia.com%2Fnational%2Fambedkar-jayanti-manu-statue-in-rajasthan-high-court-and-dalit-activists-long-demand-to-remove-it-news-191517%5C%22%3Ehas%20not%20been%20resumed%3C%2Fa%3E%20since.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20meantime%2C%20several%20Dalit%20organisations%20and%20Bahujan%20Samaj%20Party%20leaders%20have%20been%20demanding%20the%20removal%20of%20Manu%E2%80%99s%20statue.%20On%20October%208%2C%202018%2C%20two%20Ambedkarite%20women%20activists%20from%20Aurangabad%2C%20Maharashtra%20%E2%80%93%20Sheelabai%20Pawar%20and%20Kanta%20Ramesh%20Ahire%20%E2%80%93%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fkantabai-ahire-sheela-pawar-manu-statue-blackened-protest%5C%22%3E%20were%20arrested%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20throwing%20black%20paint%20on%20Manu%E2%80%99s%20statue.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20nothing%20could%20remove%20Manu%E2%80%99s%20statue.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fmanusmriti-hindu-rashtra-rss%5C%22%3EThe%20Laws%20of%20Manu%20and%20What%20They%20Would%20Mean%20for%20Citizens%20of%20the%20Hindu%20Rashtra%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Rajasthan%2C%20governments%20alternate%20between%20the%20Congress%20and%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20in%20every%20election.%20The%20BJP%20and%20the%20Rashtriya%20Swayamsevak%20Sangh%20(RSS)%E2%80%99s%20stance%20has%20often%20justified%20the%20caste%20system.%20However%2C%20why%20didn%E2%80%99t%20the%20Congress%20party%2C%20which%20claims%20to%20be%20pro-constitution%2C%20put%20its%20weight%20behind%20the%20litigation%20to%20remove%20Manu%E2%80%99s%20statue%20when%20it%20came%20to%20power%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20answer%20lies%20in%20a%20statement%20by%20Congress%20leader%20and%20head%20of%20its%20manifesto%20drafting%20committee%2C%20Vibhuti%20Bhushan%20Sharma.%20According%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fa-day-in-the-life-of-a-manu-statue-in-the-rajasthan-high-court-5421545%2F%5C%22%3ESharma%2C%20a%20former%20president%20of%20the%20Rajasthan%20High%20Court%20Bar%20Association%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20the%20statue%20of%20Manu%20was%20installed%20in%20the%20high%20court%2C%20it%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20for%20any%20particular%20caste.%20Manu%20is%20regarded%20as%20the%20first%20person%20to%20have%20come%20up%20with%20a%20written%20law.%20If%20there%20is%20any%20downside%20to%20that%20law%2C%20it%20is%20open%20to%20amendments%20as%20is%20done%20in%20our%20constitution.%20The%20statue%20shouldn%E2%80%99t%20be%20associated%20with%20any%20caste.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20irony%20is%20this%20statement%20of%20the%20Congress%20leader%20resembles%20closely%20with%20the%20statement%20of%20VHP%E2%80%99s%20Acharya%20Dharmendra%2C%20who%20had%20filed%20a%20petition%20against%20the%20removal%20of%20Manu%E2%80%99s%20statue.%20He%20had%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20a%20great%20idea%20to%20have%20a%20Manu%20statue%20inside%20the%20high%20court%20as%20he%20was%20the%20first%20person%20anywhere%20in%20the%20world%20to%20draft%20a%20law.%20Those%20who%20oppose%20him%20are%20ignorant%20of%20Manu%E2%80%99s%20philosophy.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHow%20is%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20understanding%20of%20Manu%20or%20the%20constitution%20different%20from%20the%20RSS%2C%20which%20claims%20Manusmriti%20to%20be%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20best%20constitution%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20there%20is%20any%20difference%2C%20isn%E2%80%99t%20it%20enough%20to%20preserve%20Ambedkar%E2%80%99s%20ideals%20and%20the%20constitution%20from%20the%20onslaught%20of%20Manu%2C%20the%20RSS%20and%20the%20BJP%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndifference%20of%20SC%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20has%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20responsible%20for%20protecting%20the%20constitution%2C%20done%20in%20this%20matter%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20case%20demanding%20the%20removal%20of%20Manu%E2%80%99s%20statue%20from%20the%20Rajasthan%20high%20court%20premises%20had%20been%20deliberately%20delayed%20for%20more%20than%2025%20years%2C%20several%20Dalit%20activists%20and%20organisations%20filed%20a%20PIL%20in%20the%20top%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20on%20February%2024%2C%202023%2C%20the%20division%20bench%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20comprising%20Justices%20Sanjeev%20Khanna%20and%20Justice%20Sundaresh%2C%20dismissed%20the%20petition%2C%20saying%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20do%20not%20find%20any%20good%20ground%20and%20reason%20to%20entertain%20the%20present%20writ%20petition%20as%20a%20public%20interest%20litigation%20under%20Article%2032%20of%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India%20and%20hence%2C%20the%20writ%20petition%20is%20dismissed.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20decision%20allowed%20Manu%E2%80%99s%20statue%20to%20remain.%20And%20the%20same%20court%20has%20unveiled%20the%20statue%20of%20Ambedkar%20on%20its%20own%20premises.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EManu%20and%20Manusmriti%20represent%20injustice%2C%20social%20inequality%2C%20caste%20hierarchy%2C%20and%20patriarchy.%20Ambedkar%20and%20the%20constitution%20stand%20for%20equality%2C%20compassion%2C%20socio-economic%20justice%2C%20and%20fraternity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHow%20can%20both%20coexist%3F%20How%20can%20both%20be%20symbols%20of%20the%20Indian%20judiciary%20that%20is%20tasked%20with%20protecting%20the%20constitution%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Hindutva%20forces%20have%20reinterpreted%20the%20constitution%20and%20the%20history%20to%20suit%20the%20ideals%20of%20Manusmriti%20while%20at%20the%20same%20time%20idolising%20Ambedkar%2C%20They%20have%20perhaps%20made%20this%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fsymbols-serve-oppressors-that-is-why-manu-must-fall%5C%22%3ESymbols%20Serve%20Oppressors%2C%20That%20Is%20Why%20Manu%20Must%20Fall%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EConstitution%20Day%20or%20Vedic%20Day%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETheir%20latest%20stratagem%20was%20last%20year%E2%80%99s%20order%20by%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20to%20celebrate%20November%2026%2C%20Constitution%20Adoption%20Day%2C%20around%20the%20theme%20of%20%E2%80%98India%20%E2%80%93%20the%20Mother%20of%20Democracy%E2%80%99.%20Along%20with%20this%20order%2C%20the%20Indian%20Council%20of%20Historical%20Research%20provided%20a%20conceptual%20note%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fdistorted-histories-inmother-of-democracy%5C%22%3Ewhich%20claimed%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20khap%20panchayats%20were%20institutions%20of%20democracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20Ambedkar%2C%20in%20his%20work%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.in%2FANNIHILATION-CASTE-Annotated-Critical-AMBEDKAR%2Fdp%2F8189059637%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EAnnihilation%20of%20Caste%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20had%20given%20a%20call%20to%20destroy%20the%20Vedas%2C%20Puranas%2C%20and%20Manusmriti%2C%20if%20Hinduism%20were%20to%20truly%20become%20a%20religion%2C%20and%20if%20a%20Hindu%20were%20to%20become%20a%20genuine%20human%20being%2C%20and%20if%20India%20was%20to%20become%20a%20genuine%20democracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFar%20from%20demolishing%20the%20ideals%20of%20Manusmriti%2C%20Manu%E2%80%99s%20statue%20stands%20on%20a%20court%20premises%20%E2%80%93%20with%20neither%20political%20parties%20nor%20the%20higher%20judiciary%20seemingly%20finding%20any%20contradiction%20in%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701354225000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F08%2F16155753%2FManu-Rajasthan-HC.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Findia-democracy-statue-manu-ambedkar%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20existence%20of%20Manu's%20statue%20on%20a%20court%20premises%20can%20be%20seen%20as%20a%20glorification%20of%20values%20that%20are%20against%20the%20basic%20structure%20and%20values%20of%20the%20constitution.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Findia-democracy-statue-manu-ambedkar%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Exit%20Polls%3A%20Close%20Battle%20Between%20Congress%20and%20BJP%20in%20Hindi%20Belt%3B%20BRS%20on%20Backfoot%20in%20Telangana%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F30173622%2Fchief-ministers.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20exit%20polls%20show%20a%20close%20contest%20between%20the%20Congress%20and%20the%20BJP%20in%20the%20three%20Hindi-belt%20states%20%E2%80%93%20Rajasthan%2C%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20and%20MP%20%E2%80%93%20with%20various%20agencies%20giving%20a%20slight%20edge%20to%20one%20over%20another.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20336px)%2085vw%2C%20336px%5C%22%20src%3D%5